(168, 1, '2015-01-06 07:32:43', '2015-01-06 07:32:43', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Restored and Improved Our Parks and Community Facilities</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">We have an outstanding parks system that provides fun-filled, healthy experiences and lifetime memories for our kids and families.</p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding">Unfortunately, capital maintenance and repairs to our parks and community facilities had been deferred for many years, leading to significant facilities deterioration, and in some cases, non-functional and unsafe conditions. </p>\r\n  <p class="btm_padding">Community treasures, Hamilton and Donner Centers, were particularly dilapidated and one the verge of being safety hazards.  Some neighborhood parks were badly neglected and had become havens for drug users. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown strongly believes that our parks and community facilities are indispensable and cherished community resources that must be safe, inviting and well-maintained outdoor and indoor spaces.  Under her leadership, the City:</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/parks1.png" alt="parks" width="370" height="498" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-440" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Embarked on an aggressive program to invest 5.5 million public and private dollars to preserve and improve our existing parks and community facilities, including Hamilton and Donner Centers.</li>\r\n<li>Reversed years of neglect and deterioration of our community’s most cherished facilities and ensured they are safe and inviting outdoor and indoor spacesenjoyed by today’s and future generations.  </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Parks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'parks', '', '', '2015-01-12 09:46:58', '2015-01-12 09:46:58', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=168', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(169, 1, '2015-01-06 07:32:43', '2015-01-06 07:32:43', '', 'Parks', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '168-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:32:43', '2015-01-06 07:32:43', '', 168, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/168-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(170, 1, '2015-01-06 07:32:55', '2015-01-06 07:32:55', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1>Made Columbus Safer, Protected You and Your Family</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Along with maintaining and improving our public infrastructure, public safety is job number one for Mayor Kristen Brown.<br><span class="red_color">Accelerated Law Enforcement Efforts</span> Under Mayor Brown’s leadership, we have more police officers on our streets than at any time in our city’s history and never before have they been more productive. She and her administration have:</p>\r\n    \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/safety.png" alt="safety" width="609" height="307" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-232" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Choked the flow of dangerous drugs into our community, increasing drug-related arrests by 37% last year.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically increased proactive community policing by all patrol officers and a new dedicated community policing unit, resulting a \r\n45% increase in community policing patrols.</li>\r\n<li>Significantly reduced property crime and restoring stability to our hardest-hit neighborhoods.</li>\r\n<li>Reduced the number of traffic accidents through an acceleration of traffic enforcement efforts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Emergency Medical Services and Saved Tax Dollars</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown and her team have significantly advanced emergency medical services, ensuring residents have the best chance for surviving a life-threatening event.  The City has:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Awarded a new ambulance contract to Columbus Regional Hospital after conducting a fair, transparent and competitive bidding processresulting in significantly improved service and reduced costs to taxpayers from nearly $1 million every year to $0 a year.</li>\r\n<li>ncreased the number of paramedic firefighterscertified in advanced life-support techniques tostaff one on all six engines at every fire station every day.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>ImprovedRescue, Disaster and Extreme Weather Response</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown has ensured that we are well prepared for the myriad of threats our community faces.  Mayor Brown and her team:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sold the mayor’s city-owned vehicle to fund ice water rescue equipment for City firefighters to ensure optimal victim survivability around the city’s 161 ponds and lakes.</li>\r\n<li>Unveiled the first-ever Flood Risk Warning and Management Plan on the fifth tanniversary of the 2008 flood. Never again will we be unprepared.</li>\r\n<li>Deployed an emergency notification system that sends alerts to citizens by voicemail, text messages and emails during emergencies.</li>\r\n<li>Ensured that our roads were cleared of snow and ice and potholes were patched in a timely manner during extreme winter weather the last two years.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Public Safety', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'public-safetyt', '', '', '2015-01-12 09:48:10', '2015-01-12 09:48:10', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=170', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(171, 1, '2015-01-06 07:32:55', '2015-01-06 07:32:55', '', 'Public Safetyt', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:32:55', '2015-01-06 07:32:55', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(172, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:06', '2015-01-06 07:33:06', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Revitalized and Strengthened Our Neighborhoods</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">Mayor Kristen Brown has taken a comprehensive approach to revitalization and made tremendous progress making our more challenged neighborhoods safer, prouder and free of blight.  Since assuming office, she and her administration have:</p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Neighborhoods.png" alt="Neighborhoods" width="988" height="496" /></div>\r\n<ul class="top_padding">\r\n<li>Substantially improved conditions in our neighborhoods through regular neighborhood meetings, community policing, cleanup projects, and code enforcement.</li>\r\n<li>Turned 9th Street Neighborhood Park into a safe and inviting place for kids to play from what it had become: a magnet for anti-social behavior and criminal activity, particularly drug-related issues.</li>\r\n<li>Ordered the demolishment or repair of twenty-three abandoned, blighted and unsafe homes and commercial buildings.</li>\r\n<li>Begun the City’s first ever Blight Elimination Program with a $760,000 grant to fund the demolishment of approximately three dozen abandoned and blighted houses.</li>\r\n<li>Completed the State Street Revitalization Plan to redevelop State Street and revitalize the surrounding neighborhoods. Mayor Brown voted in favor of funding and implementing the first phase of the State Street Plan this year.</li>\r\n<li>Partnered with two private developers to remediate and redevelop the Golden Castings Foundry site, a decade-long source of blight in the heart of our city.  The redevelopment will provide much-needed addition high-quality, affordable housing and an assisted living facility.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Neighborhoods', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'neighborhoods', '', '', '2015-01-12 09:48:50', '2015-01-12 09:48:50', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=172', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(173, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:06', '2015-01-06 07:33:06', '', 'Neighborhoods', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:33:06', '2015-01-06 07:33:06', '', 172, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(174, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:18', '2015-01-06 07:33:18', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Encouraged Job Growth</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">\r\n Under Mayor Kristen Brown’s leadership, Columbus has set records for the number of jobs and employment.  The </p>\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">Columbus metropolitan area is at all-time record highs for both the number of jobs in our community – more than \r\n51,000 - and the number of residents who are employed – more than 41,000.   Our unemployment rate is currently \r\nonly 4% - the second lowest in the state.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="inner_text_container full_width btm_padding1 "><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/jobs1.png" alt="jobs" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-535" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set all-time records for jobs and employment, second lowest unemployment rate in the state.</li>\r\n<li>Reaffirmed Cummins’ commitment to Columbus with announcement of 500 new jobs.</li>\r\n<li>Encouraged the creation of more than another 500 new industrial jobs and investments of nearly $250 million.</li>\r\n<li>Provided tax incentives, encouraging the creation of more than another 500 new jobs and investments of nearly $250 million.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a preliminary plan to redevelop the nearly 600 acres of the former Walesboro Airport into an industrial park to provide shovel-ready industrial sites for continued job-creating growth.ts.</li>\r\n<li>Developed the city’s first Strategic Growth Plan to readily and efficiently accommodate the city’s growth outside today’s city limits.</li>\r\n<li>Formed a public-private partnership to develop a 114-bed, $5 million student housing complex at the airport.  This is the “game-changer” for our four colleges’ recruitment efforts and our ability to produce a steady pipeline of skilled and educated workers that our employers need to prosper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Jobs', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'jobs', '', '', '2015-01-13 04:00:00', '2015-01-13 04:00:00', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=174', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(175, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:18', '2015-01-06 07:33:18', '', 'Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:33:18', '2015-01-06 07:33:18', '', 174, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(176, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in New Era of Good Government</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"> \r\n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And she’s delivering.  Mayor Brown and her administration have: </p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin btm_padding1"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government1.png" alt="government" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-530" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operated transparently, responsively, ethically and with accountability.</li>\r\n<li>Dissolved the City’s private corporation, CDI, and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors.</li>\r\n<li>Began live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings on the internet.</li>\r\n<li>Passed comprehensive code of ethical conduct.</li>\r\n<li>Attained national accreditation by the Columbus Police Department.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically improved city government’s transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.</li>\r\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest — not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.</li>\r\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status.</li>\r\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'good-government', '', '', '2015-01-13 03:44:38', '2015-01-13 03:44:38', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=176', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(177, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '2015-01-06 07:33:29', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(178, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Made the Tough Calls and Got Our Fiscal House in Order</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Kristen Brown understands she works for the taxpayers who write the checks to local government, not for the “special interests” who cash the checks. </p>\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Mayor Brown has been shaping city government’s organization and budget to lower taxes and fees, best advance your priorities and ensure city government gets the most for your dollar.  This has resulted in changes in the way city government does business and a more streamlined, priority-driven budget. </p>\r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><a href="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/a-record-of-sucess-Fiscal-Responsibility1.png"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/a-record-of-sucess-Fiscal-Responsibility1.png" alt="a-record-of-sucess-Fiscal-Responsibility" width="495" height="349" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-250" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<h2>Eliminated Mandatory Fees and Championed a Decrease in Property Taxes</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Repealed the mandatory trash fees from residents’ utility bills, returning $1.4 million a year to our citizens.</li>\r\n<li>Voted to return $3 million of TIF property tax revenues to the taxpayers to reduce property tax rates.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Changed Spending Priorities</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Terminated the expensive and problematic outdoor sports complex.</li>\r\n<li>nvested in repairing and restoring existing infrastructure, roads and public parks and community facilities, not developing new facilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Saved Taxpayers Money</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Conducted competitive purchasing processes for services and consolidated purchasing of supplies and equipment, saving taxpayers more than a million dollars a year.</li>\r\n<li>Saved more than $500,000 annually by decreasing taxpayers’ share of rising employee health care costs.</li>\r\n<li>Terminated the personal use of city vehicles except for police and fire.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Maintained Financial Strength</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>ssued no incremental new debt and maintained healthy cash reserves.</li>\r\n<li>Maintained Standard and Poor’s very strong credit rating of a AA-.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Fiscal Responsibility', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fiscal-responsibility', '', '', '2015-01-12 09:51:41', '2015-01-12 09:51:41', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=178', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(179, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '', 'Fiscal Responsibility', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '178-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '2015-01-06 07:33:41', '', 178, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/178-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(180, 1, '2015-01-06 07:33:52', '2015-01-06 07:33:52', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Met Demand for Expanded Services With No Tax Increase</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">Mayor Kristen Brown has met the community’s demand for expanded City services  with no increase in taxes and after eliminated the mandatory trash fees. Kristen Brown has met the community’s demand for expanded City services Mayor Kristen Brown has met the community’s demand for expanded City services</p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Services1.png" alt="Services" width="1002" height="382" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-442" /></div>\r\n<ul class="top_padding">\r\n<li>Began no-fee residential curbside recycling program.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved 100-percent adoption rate for healthy dogs the last three years.</li>\r\n<li>Added a fifth transit route to and from the ever-growing west side.</li>\r\n<li>Dedicated police officers to the schools to keep our kids safe.</li>\r\n<li>Began cost-sharing program with homeowners to repair sidewalks and curbs.</li>\r\n<li>Curbside Recycling - Formed a public-private partnership enabling the City to provide a curbside recycling service for residents for no additional fees.  Service begins in February of 2015 with free 96 gallon toters for single-stream collection, no sorting required.</li>\r\n<li>Animal Care Services –Achieved a 100-percent adoption rate for healthy dogs for the last three years.  Animal Care Services has for the first time found all dogs loving, permanent homes, eliminating the need for euthanasia due to space constraints at our shelter.  Adoptions of both dogs and cats are at all-time highs.</li>\r\n<li>Transit Service – Added a fifth transit route to include service to and from the west side on SR 46 and expanded week-day hours of all routes to 8 pm.  These changes were the first and second most requested service improvements by transit customers.</li>\r\n<li>School Resource Officers - In partnership with the school system, dedicated two police officers in the schools to improve our kids’ safety and to encourage children and teens to avoid drugs, bullying and violence.</li>\r\n<li>Shared Cost Sidewalk and Curb Program – Introduced the Shared Cost Sidewalk and Curb Program, a cost-sharing program for homeowners to address overdue repairs to sidewalks and curbs.  The program offers outstanding value to homeowners and increases the safety and appearances of our neighborhoods.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Expanded Services', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'expanded-services', '', '', '2015-01-12 09:52:14', '2015-01-12 09:52:14', '', 10, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/?page_id=180', 0, 'page', '', 0),
