(434, 1, '2015-01-10 05:15:16', '2015-01-10 05:15:16', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1>Made Columbus Safer, Protected You and Your Family</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="blue_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n  <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n    <p class="btm_padding">Along with maintaining and improving our public infrastructure, public safety is job number one for Mayor Kristen Brown.<br><span class="red_color">Accelerated Law Enforcement Efforts</span> Under Mayor Brown’s leadership, we have more police officers on our streets than at any time in our city’s history and never before have they been more productive. She and her administration have:</p>\r\n    \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="img_container"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/safety.png" alt="safety" width="609" height="307" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-232" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Choked the flow of dangerous drugs into our community, increasing drug-related arrests by 37% last year.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically increased proactive community policing by all patrol officers and a new dedicated community policing unit, resulting a \r\n45% increase in community policing patrols.</li>\r\n<li>Significantly reduced property crime and restoring stability to our hardest-hit neighborhoods.</li>\r\n<li>Reduced the number of traffic accidents through an acceleration of traffic enforcement efforts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>Improved Emergency Medical Services and Saved Tax Dollars</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown and her team have significantly advanced emergency medical services, ensuring residents have the best chance for surviving a life-threatening event.  The City has:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Awarded a new ambulance contract to Columbus Regional Hospital after conducting a fair, transparent and competitive bidding processresulting in significantly improved service and reduced costs to taxpayers from nearly $1 million every year to $0 a year.</li>\r\n<li>ncreased the number of paramedic firefighterscertified in advanced life-support techniques tostaff one on all six engines at every fire station every day.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<h2>ImprovedRescue, Disaster and Extreme Weather Response</h2>\r\n<p>Mayor Kristen Brown has ensured that we are well prepared for the myriad of threats our community faces.  Mayor Brown and her team:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sold the mayor’s city-owned vehicle to fund ice water rescue equipment for City firefighters to ensure optimal victim survivability around the city’s 161 ponds and lakes.</li>\r\n<li>Unveiled the first-ever Flood Risk Warning and Management Plan on the fifth tanniversary of the 2008 flood. Never again will we be unprepared.</li>\r\n<li>Deployed an emergency notification system that sends alerts to citizens by voicemail, text messages and emails during emergencies.</li>\r\n<li>Ensured that our roads were cleared of snow and ice and potholes were patched in a timely manner during extreme winter weather the last two years.</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Public Safety', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '170-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-10 05:15:16', '2015-01-10 05:15:16', '', 170, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/170-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(435, 1, '2015-01-10 05:20:56', '2015-01-10 05:20:56', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n<h1 class="red_color ">Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</h1>\r\n<div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>     \r\n <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n        <p class="blue_color_normal">We are one of the safest communities in the country. However, when it comes to our personal safety and the protection of our property, there will always be room for improvement. A healthy community includes living healthy lifestyles and living in an </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_part full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_blue_container">\r\n          <p class="blue_color_normal">environmentally safe community.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding blue_color_normal">Mayor Kristen Brown’s goals for a safe and healthy community include:</p>\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Safest Community</h2>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1">Goal:  Be the safest city of our size in the country.</p>\r\n          <p class=" btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown’s plan calls for sustaining and advancing your and your family’s safety as her highest priority.</p>\r\n          <p >Thankfully, our violent crime is in the lowest ten percent of the nation.  However, dangerous drugs are prevalent in our community.  Not only does drug abuse destroy the lives of users and families, it is fueling a property crime rate that is unacceptably high.  Mayor Brown’s priority is to:</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="img_container top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/health1.png" alt="health" width="441" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-410" /></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin ">\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>Stem the tide of dangerous drugs into our community and cut our property crime rate by continuing to accelerate our narcotics investigations and community policing efforts and by leveraging technology as a force multiplier.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class="community_btmPart full_width ">\r\n        <div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n          <h2>Healthy Community</h2>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" >Goal:  Radically improve the health and wellness of our residents through healthy behaviors, healthy lifestyles and access to healthcare.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding" >Obesity, substance abuse and mental illness remain the most vexing health problems facing us today.  We’re making great progress on these fronts but we have much more work to do.</p>\r\n          <p class="top_padding btm_padding1" >Mayor Kristen Brown’s plan ensures that the community collectively supports both mental and physical wellness. </p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Cut the demand for drugs in our community through significantly greater leadership and resources directed toward prevention and treatment of substance abuse and mental health disorders.  Cutting the supply of drugs will remain a tremendous challenge until we seriously address the demand for drugs in our community.</li>\r\n            <li>Build People Bridges, dedicated bike and pedestrian bridges, to make important and safe People Trail connections over our rivers, busy streets and railroad tracks, including the riverfront of the Pump House property, over Lindsey into downtown at the 3rd Street Bridge and over Haw Creek and Central near 3rd Street. </li>\r\n            <li>Form a public-private partnership to develop an indoor athletic training facility on the airport’s property for use by our local sports teams, including soccer, football and other field sports teams.</li>            \r\n          </ul>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>', 'Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '297-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-10 05:20:56', '2015-01-10 05:20:56', '', 297, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/297-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
