(451, 1, '2015-01-10 05:55:13', '2015-01-10 05:55:13', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance Opportunities for All</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Quality Neighborhoods and Housing for All</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Goal:   Ensure safe and proud neighborhoods and quality affordable housing for all.\r\nMayor Kristen Brown’s plan revitalizes and strengthens our neighborhoods and business corridors by the elimination of blight and through rehabilitation and redevelopment, including the development of quality affordable housing.</p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Opportunities1.png" alt="Opportunities" width="998" height="374" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-450" /></div>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Revitalize and Redevelop State Street Corridor according to our plan.</li>\r\n<li>Revitalize our neighborhoods through infrastructure improvements, stronger property maintenance codes, code enforcement, blight elimination programs, neighborhood cleanups and incentives for private investment in targeted revitalization areas.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Increase the number of affordable housing units in our community through public-private partnerships.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Advance Opportunities for All', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '270-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-10 05:55:13', '2015-01-10 05:55:13', '', 270, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/270-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(452, 1, '2015-01-10 05:56:59', '2015-01-10 05:56:59', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">Advance Opportunities for All</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n          <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">Quality Neighborhoods and Housing for All</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Goal:   Ensure safe and proud neighborhoods and quality affordable housing for all.\r\nMayor Kristen Brown’s plan revitalizes and strengthens our neighborhoods and business corridors by the elimination of blight and through rehabilitation and redevelopment, including the development of quality affordable housing.</p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Opportunities1.png" alt="Opportunities" width="998" height="374" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-450" /></div>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="inner_text_container full_width top_padding">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Revitalize and Redevelop State Street Corridor according to our plan.</li>\r\n<li>Revitalize our neighborhoods through infrastructure improvements, stronger property maintenance codes, code enforcement, blight elimination programs, neighborhood cleanups and incentives for private investment in targeted revitalization areas.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Increase the number of affordable housing units in our community through public-private partnerships.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Advance Opportunities for All', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '270-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-10 05:56:59', '2015-01-10 05:56:59', '', 270, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/270-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(453, 1, '2015-01-10 06:00:12', '2015-01-10 06:00:12', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n<h1 class="red_color ">Good Government Values</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width top_margin">\r\n     <p class="btm_padding blue_color_normal">Mayor Kristen Brown has ushered in a new era of good government and led the development a set of core values for City officials and employees that embody the principles of good government.\r\nOur values are important because they provide the foundation for how we pursue our vision.  How we get there is every bit as important as getting there.</p><div class="inner_text_container full_width"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/value.png" alt="value" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-398" /></div>\r\n     </div><div class="inner_value full_width top_margin">    \r\n<ul>\r\n<li><h2>INTEGRITY WITHOUT COMPROMISE</h2></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">We are honest and ethical in all we say and do. We honor our word and keep our commitments. </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><h2>PROFESSIONALISM</h2></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">We treat every person with respect, dignity and equity. We are positive, courteous, conscientious and businesslike in all of our actions.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><h2>CUSTOMER FIRST</h2></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">We put the needs of our customers, the people of Columbus, at the heart of everything we do. We strive to be responsive and exceed their expectations at all times. </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><h2>PEOPLE WORKING TOGETHER</h2></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">We care deeply about our people and recognize them as our most valuable asset. We work as a team across all boundaries.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><h2>OPENNESS</h2></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">We are receptive and accessible and our work is transparent. </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><h2>ACCOUNTABILITY</h2></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">We take responsibility for our actions and for delivering results.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><h2>FISCAL RESPONSIBILITY</h2></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="btm_padding">We get the most from the taxpayer’s dollar. We live within our means. We are fiscally very solid.</p>\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n', 'Good Government Values', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '273-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-10 06:00:12', '2015-01-10 06:00:12', '', 273, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/273-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(454, 1, '2015-01-10 06:19:53', '2015-01-10 06:19:53', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">A Plan for the Future:  Advance Columbus</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n     <div class="inner_blue_container"><p class="btm_padding">Our community is a special and remarkable combination of people and place.  World-renown architecture is woven into the fabric of our daily lives. We benefit from exciting cultural and recreational amenities, a diverse population, a strong sense of community and teamwork and a commitment to excellence. </p>\r\n     <p>Our local economy is a powerhouse relative to the rest of the state and nation.  The number of jobs in our community is at an all-time high.  The number of residents employed is also at an all-time high.</p></div>\r\n     <div class="plan_rightPart"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/plan.png" alt="plan" width="438" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-266" /></div>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width">\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">By every major measure, our quality of life in Columbus, Indiana is far better than the state and even the nation as a whole.\r\nBut we are Columbus.  We aim even higher and we have an unshakable confidence in our ability to create an even more remarkable future.</p>\r\n     <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">OUR VISION</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Our vision is <strong>“to be the very best community of its size in the country.” </strong> It is a bold and ambitious vision.</p>\r\n     <h2 class="blue_color btm_padding1 ">ONE CITY. ONE PLAN. ADVANCE COLUMBUS.</h2>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">In order to advance Columbus toward this future, Mayor Kristen Brown partnered with the leaders of several other public and private organizations dedicated to serving our community. Together with much public engagement, they created “Advance Columbus,” a roadmap to solve our toughest challenges, leverage our greatest strengths and capitalize on our many opportunities to advance our quality of life for today and for future generations. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown rolled out Advance Columbus at her State of the City address in 2013. </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">She also made it the City of Columbus’ mission to do its part in advancing Columbus toward the future we envision.  Last year, Mayor Brown and department heads developed the City government’s first strategic plan, aligning the city government’s priorities with the community’s highest priorities as defined by Advance Columbus.  </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">The plan’s priorities are to: </p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">1.   Advance Quality Infrastructure<br>\r\n2.   Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs<br>\r\n3.   Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">Recognizing that how we get there is every bit as important as getting there, Mayor Brown’s plan importantly includes advancing Columbus in a way that is consistent with the <a href="">values of good government.</a> </p>\r\n\r\n     </div>', 'Advance Columbus', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '292-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-10 06:19:53', '2015-01-10 06:19:53', '', 292, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/292-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(455, 1, '2015-01-10 06:53:41', '2015-01-10 06:53:41', '', 'about_img4', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'about_img4', '', '', '2015-01-10 06:53:41', '2015-01-10 06:53:41', '', 14, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/about_img4.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(456, 1, '2015-01-10 08:04:10', '2015-01-10 08:04:10', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Mayor Kristen Brown</h1>\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\n<div class="inner_blue_container">\n<h2 class="top_margin">A Hometown Girl with a Passion for Columbus</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Mayor Kristen Brown is a native of Columbus with humble beginnings.  She has deep roots in the community: a sixth generation resident of Bartholomew County on her mother’s side of the family and a fourth generation resident of Columbus on her father’s side.</li>\n<li>Mayor Brown’s love for Columbus, her passion to serve the people and her capability and courage to make a positive difference led her to run for mayor of her hometown.</li>\n</ul></div>\n<div class="img_container top_margin"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/about_img41.png" alt="about_img4" width="552" height="353" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-480" /></div>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\n<h2 >A Champion of the People Elected with Mandate for Change</h2>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_padding"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/about_img31.png" alt="about_img3" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-482" /></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Kristen Brown was elected the 36th Mayor of the City of Columbus in a wave of popular support in 2011.  She won the Republican primary in a landslide and by a margin of 3:1 over both of the political establishment’s picks on the Republican ticket.  She then won the general election by a margin of more than 2 to 1 and after receiving more votes than any mayoral candidate in the city’s history.  </li>\n<li>Voters placed their confidence in Kristen Brown to make government better and more inclusive and to advance Columbus toward an even brighter future.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_padding">\n<h2 >A Public Servant Who Has Kept Her Promises and More</h2>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_padding"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/about_img1.png" alt="about_img1" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-484" /></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Since assuming office on January 1, 2012, she has delivered on every one of her campaign promises and more.  </li>\n<li>Mayor Brown has lowered taxes, improved services, particularly public safety, provided the environment that ensures our employers prosper and create good jobs, made the tough calls to get our fiscal house in order and made city government accountable and ensured it operates with integrity, transparency a strong citizen voice.</li>\n<li>She has also invested in vital public infrastructure, repairing our roads and parks facilities and reversing years of deferred investment and neglect.  She’s strengthened our neighborhoods and eliminated blight.  She’s met the community’s demand for expanded services with no tax increase.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_padding">\n<div class="inner_blue_container">\n<h2 >A Leader with Vision and a Plan</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Mayor Brown, in partnership with the community, developed Columbus’ first community-wide strategic plan and process, “Advance Columbus.”  Advance Columbus paints a bold vision for Columbus, defines the community’s highest strategic priorities, leaving no one behind, and sets out the solutions and processes for advancing Columbus toward its vision.  Advance Columbus is already achieving tangible results.</li>\n</ul></div>\n<div class="img_container "><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/about_img5.png" alt="about_img5" width="552" height="353" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-474" /></div>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_padding">\n<h2 >A Proven, Qualified Leader</h2>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_padding"></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Prior to serving as Mayor, Mayor Brown came from a successful career in business, holding numerous positions of increasing responsibility in the fields of banking, investment management and the computer software industry.  Brown was a senior executive and Vice President of several leading companies including publicly-traded giants Oracle and Intuit, the developer of Quickbooks, Quicken and TurboTax.</li>\n<li>Brown graduated at the top of her class from Columbus North High School in 1982. She graduated from Brown University with a B.A., magna cum laude, in 1986 and from Harvard University with an M.B.A in 1993.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'About Kristen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '14-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-10 08:04:10', '2015-01-10 08:04:10', '', 14, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/14-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
