(528, 1, '2015-01-12 08:51:16', '2015-01-12 08:51:16', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">You Can Help</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin ">\r\n<p class="btm_padding1 " >Together, we took back our community in the mayor’s race in 2011.  In the Republican primary on this May 5th, the choices are clear.  We can go back to politics as usual and taking your tax dollars or we can continue to positively change our government’s course, protect your tax dollars and advance Columbus toward our vision.  </p>\r\n<p  class="btm_padding" >But we need you again to make it happen and we hope you’ll join our team.  \r\n  </p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n', 'You Can Help', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-12 08:51:16', '2015-01-12 08:51:16', '', 16, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(529, 1, '2015-01-12 09:33:26', '2015-01-12 09:33:26', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n        <h1 class="red_color ">A Plan for the Future:  Advance Columbus</h1>\r\n        <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n      </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n     <div class="inner_blue_container"><p class="btm_padding">Our community is a special and remarkable combination of people and place.  World-renown architecture is woven into the fabric of our daily lives. We benefit from exciting cultural and recreational amenities, a diverse population, a strong sense of community and teamwork and a commitment to excellence. </p>\r\n     <p>Our local economy is a powerhouse relative to the rest of the state and nation.  The number of jobs in our community is at an all-time high.  The number of residents employed is also at an all-time high.</p></div>\r\n     <div class="plan_rightPart"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/plan1.png" alt="plan" width="438" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-511" /></div>\r\n     </div>\r\n     <div class="plan_inner_part full_width">\r\n     <p class="btm_padding top_margin">By every major measure, our quality of life in Columbus, Indiana is far better than the state and even the nation as a whole.\r\nBut we are Columbus.  We aim even higher and we have an unshakable confidence in our ability to create an even more remarkable future.</p>\r\n     <h2 class="red_color btm_padding1">OUR VISION</h2>\r\n     <p class="btm_padding">Our vision is <strong>“to be the very best community of its size in the country.” </strong> It is a bold and ambitious vision.</p>\r\n     <h2 class="blue_color btm_padding1 ">ONE CITY. ONE PLAN. ADVANCE COLUMBUS.</h2>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">In order to advance Columbus toward this future, Mayor Kristen Brown partnered with the leaders of several other public and private organizations dedicated to serving our community. Together with much public engagement, they created “Advance Columbus,” a roadmap to solve our toughest challenges, leverage our greatest strengths and capitalize on our many opportunities to advance our quality of life for today and for future generations. </p>\r\n      <p class="btm_padding1">Mayor Kristen Brown rolled out Advance Columbus at her State of the City address in 2013. </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">She also made it the City of Columbus’ mission to do its part in advancing Columbus toward the future we envision.  Last year, Mayor Brown and department heads developed the City government’s first strategic plan, aligning the city government’s priorities with the community’s highest priorities as defined by Advance Columbus.  </p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1 blue_color_normal">The plan’s priorities are to: </p>\r\n<p class="btm_padding1">1.   Advance Quality Infrastructure<br>\r\n2.   Advance Economic Prosperity and Well-Paying Jobs<br>\r\n3.   Advance the Safety and Health of Our Community</p>\r\n            <p class="btm_padding1">Recognizing that how we get there is every bit as important as getting there, Mayor Brown’s plan importantly includes advancing Columbus in a way that is consistent with the <a href="">values of good government.</a> </p>\r\n\r\n     </div>', 'A Plan for the Future', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-12 09:33:26', '2015-01-12 09:33:26', '', 12, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/12-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(530, 1, '2015-01-13 03:43:47', '2015-01-13 03:43:47', '', 'government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'government-2', '', '', '2015-01-13 03:43:47', '2015-01-13 03:43:47', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government1.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(531, 1, '2015-01-13 03:43:51', '2015-01-13 03:43:51', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in New Era of Good Government</h1>\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"> \n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And she’s delivering.  Mayor Brown and her administration have: </p>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin btm_padding1"></div>\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\n<ul>\n<li>Operated transparently, responsively, ethically and with accountability.</li>\n<li>Dissolved the City’s private corporation, CDI, and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors.</li>\n<li>Began live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings on the internet.</li>\n<li>Passed comprehensive code of ethical conduct.</li>\n<li>Attained national accreditation by the Columbus Police Department.</li>\n<li>Dramatically improved city government’s transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.</li>\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest — not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.</li>\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status.</li>\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services.</li>\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\n\n\n</ul>\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-13 03:43:51', '2015-01-13 03:43:51', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(532, 1, '2015-01-13 03:44:00', '2015-01-13 03:44:00', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in New Era of Good Government</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"> \r\n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And she’s delivering.  Mayor Brown and her administration have: </p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin btm_padding1"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government1.png" alt="government" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-530" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operated transparently, responsively, ethically and with accountability.</li>\r\n<li>Dissolved the City’s private corporation, CDI, and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors.</li>\r\n<li>Began live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings on the internet.</li>\r\n<li>Passed comprehensive code of ethical conduct.</li>\r\n<li>Attained national accreditation by the Columbus Police Department.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically improved city government’s transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.</li>\r\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest — not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.</li>\r\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status.</li>\r\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-13 03:44:00', '2015-01-13 03:44:00', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(533, 1, '2015-01-13 03:44:38', '2015-01-13 03:44:38', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Ushered in New Era of Good Government</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin"> \r\n    <p>Mayor Kristen Brown believes that how government operates is every bit as important as what it accomplishes.  Her goal is to be the most honest, transparent, inclusive, responsive and accountable municipal government of our size.  And she’s delivering.  Mayor Brown and her administration have: </p>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width top_margin btm_padding1"><img src="http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/government1.png" alt="government" width="1001" height="320" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-530" /></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width ">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Operated transparently, responsively, ethically and with accountability.</li>\r\n<li>Dissolved the City’s private corporation, CDI, and stopped spending taxpayer money behind closed doors.</li>\r\n<li>Began live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings on the internet.</li>\r\n<li>Passed comprehensive code of ethical conduct.</li>\r\n<li>Attained national accreditation by the Columbus Police Department.</li>\r\n<li>Dramatically improved city government’s transparency with live and on-demand broadcasting of public meetings online. This service has attracted thousands of views.</li>\r\n<li>Gained adoption of a comprehensive code of ethical conduct, helping assure you that public officials and employees are operating in your best interest — not in their own personal interests or in favor of special interests.</li>\r\n<li>Attained accreditation for the police department, ensuring our officers maintain the highest professional standards and operate with the utmost integrity, transparency and accountability.  Only three percent of the law enforcement agencies in the nation achieve this status.</li>\r\n<li>Improved service by launching uReport, an online customer service request application that gives you the opportunity to quickly and easily request city services.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a long-term strategic plan for city government with priorities and measurable objectives and published annual reports detailing results.</li>\r\n<li>Achieved a finding-free audit from the Indiana State Board of Accounts in 2013.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>', 'Good Government', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-13 03:44:38', '2015-01-13 03:44:38', '', 176, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/176-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(534, 1, '2015-01-13 03:59:22', '2015-01-13 03:59:22', '<div class="main_heading full_width">\r\n  <h1 class="red_color ">Encouraged Job Growth</h1>\r\n  <div class="main_headingBorder"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<p class="top_margin">\r\n Under Mayor Kristen Brown’s leadership, Columbus has set records for the number of jobs and employment.  The </p>\r\n    <p class="btm_padding1">Columbus metropolitan area is at all-time record highs for both the number of jobs in our community – more than \r\n51,000 - and the number of residents who are employed – more than 41,000.   Our unemployment rate is currently \r\nonly 4% - the second lowest in the state.</p> \r\n  </div>\r\n  <div class="inner_text_container full_width btm_padding1 "><img src="images/jobs.png"></div>\r\n<div class="inner_text_container full_width">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set all-time records for jobs and employment, second lowest unemployment rate in the state.</li>\r\n<li>Reaffirmed Cummins’ commitment to Columbus with announcement of 500 new jobs.</li>\r\n<li>Encouraged the creation of more than another 500 new industrial jobs and investments of nearly $250 million.</li>\r\n<li>Provided tax incentives, encouraging the creation of more than another 500 new jobs and investments of nearly $250 million.</li>\r\n<li>Developed a preliminary plan to redevelop the nearly 600 acres of the former Walesboro Airport into an industrial park to provide shovel-ready industrial sites for continued job-creating growth.ts.</li>\r\n<li>Developed the city’s first Strategic Growth Plan to readily and efficiently accommodate the city’s growth outside today’s city limits.</li>\r\n<li>Formed a public-private partnership to develop a 114-bed, $5 million student housing complex at the airport.  This is the “game-changer” for our four colleges’ recruitment efforts and our ability to produce a steady pipeline of skilled and educated workers that our employers need to prosper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', 'Jobs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '174-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-13 03:59:22', '2015-01-13 03:59:22', '', 174, 'http://localhost/brown-for-columbus/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
